5 Widgets
*********

The dialog description language is a simple XML-like markup capable of
describing complex dialog boxes containing widgets and containers.

   Widgets are GUI elements such as buttons, entry fields, lists, and
labels.  Widgets are configured by placing sub-elements between their
opening and closing tags (*note Widget Sub-elements::).  Widgets must be
placed inside containers (*note Containers::).

* Menu:

* text::
* button::
* entry::
* checkbox::
* radiobutton::
* togglebutton::
* switch::
* combobox::
* comboboxtext::
* comboboxentry::
* list::
