5.16 ‘<pixmap>’ -- Static image
===============================

Displays a static image.  The image file is specified with ‘<input
type="file">’.  Gtkdialog3 searches for the file in directories listed
in the ‘GTKDIALOG_PIXMAP_PATH’ environment variable if it cannot be
opened directly.

   Refreshing the widget reloads the image, which is useful for
displaying dynamically generated graphics.

From ‘examples/pixmap/pixmap’:
     <pixmap>
         <input type="file">help.png</input>
     </pixmap>


