7.9.21 ‘set:WIDGET.PROPERTY=VALUE’
----------------------------------

Sets a GTK property on the named widget at runtime.  The argument is
parsed as WIDGET‘.’PROPERTY‘=’VALUE, where WIDGET is the variable name,
PROPERTY is any GTK property that the widget supports, and VALUE is the
new value.  The same properties that work as tag attributes at widget
creation time (e.g. ‘title’, ‘sensitive’, ‘label’) can be set with this
action.

     Set the window title:
     <action>set:myWindow.title=Processing...</action>

     Disable a widget:
     <action>set:myButton.sensitive=false</action>

     Using attribute syntax:
     <action type='set'>myButton.sensitive=false</action>

   This action can replace the common pattern of writing to a temporary
file and then refreshing a widget.  For example, loading a URL in a
webview:

     Before (two actions + temp file):
     <action>echo https://lwn.net > /tmp/nav</action>
     <action>refresh:webPage</action>

     After (one action, no temp file):
     <action>set:webPage.uri=https://lwn.net</action>



